methodologies, recon, proxy, fuzzing, scanners, sqli, xss, api, graphql, auth, advanced-vulns, cms, js-intel, cloud, cicd, secrets, race-conditions, desync, cache-attacks, browser-sec, business-logic, mobile-web, evasion, attack-chains, correlation, prioritization, wordlists, labs, opsec, legal, reporting, cvss, mcp, ai-memory, agents, roadmap. Read individually as needed.

## Reporting

Always use the agnostic Python generator (works in any environment):

```bash
python3 scripts/generate_report.py --input findings.json --format docx --output report.docx
python3 scripts/generate_report.py --input findings.json --format all  --output ./out/
```

Formats: md, txt, html, docx, pdf, pptx, json, all. Input schema in `assets/example_findings.json`.

## Operational rules

- Commands the user copies must be single-line, no `\` continuation, no leading whitespace.
- Add a browser User-Agent in any Python/curl scripts to avoid CloudFront/AWS WAF blocking python-requests.
- An unexpected HTTP 404 where 401/403 was expected = likely BOLA confirmed.
- Justified text in reports, no em-dashes in body, Spanish text with proper accents.
- CVSS 3.1 + 4.0 (both) per finding. CWE mandatory.

## Anti-patterns

- ❌ Skipping the methodology boot question.
- ❌ Reporting without CWE / without CVSS / without reproducible PoC.
- ❌ Running massive scans without confirmed scope.
- ❌ Em-dashes in body text (titles only).

